{
  "texts": [
    "Ultra Performance Liquid Chromatography-Quadrupole-Time of Flight/Mass Spectrometry analysis of Qiju granules",
    "The Ultra Performance Liquid Chromatography-Quadrupole-Time of Flight/Mass Spectrometry (UPLC-Q-TOF/MS) instrument was set to a capillary voltage of 2.5 kV (negative ion mode), sample cone voltage of 40 V, source temperature of 120 • C, desolvation temperature of 500 • C, and desolvation gas flow of 1000 L/h.",
    "Collision energy was set at 6 eV, and the full scan spectra were recorded from 50 to 1200 Da.",
    "Qiju granules were dissolved in purified water at a concentration of 100 mg/ml, and the solution was centrifuged to obtain the supernatant.",
    "The supernatant was analyzed by UPLC using reversed-phase C18 analytical columns (2.1 × 100 mm) packed with silica beads of 1.6 µm diameter (Cortecs R UPLC R T3, Waters, SYNAPT G2-Si, USA)."
  ]
}